WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.234 --> 00:00:06.736
[rain falling]

2
00:00:09.697 --> 00:00:11.657
[horse neighing]

3
00:00:12.908 --> 00:00:14.910
[Dunk grunting]

4
00:00:26.088 --> 00:00:28.090
[distant thunder rumbling]

5
00:00:33.429 --> 00:00:35.056
- [whispering] Hey.
- [horse nickering]

6
00:00:38.392 --> 00:00:39.894
[grunting]

7
00:00:46.901 --> 00:00:49.904
- [thunder rumbling]
- [horse neighing]

8
00:00:51.655 --> 00:00:52.656
[grunting]

9
00:00:56.243 --> 00:00:57.536
[sighs]

10
00:01:02.291 --> 00:01:04.043
I don't know the right words.

11
00:01:06.629 --> 00:01:08.172
Ought to be a septon here.

12
00:01:14.929 --> 00:01:16.305
You were a true knight.

13
00:01:18.432 --> 00:01:20.266
You never beat me
when I didn't deserve it.

14
00:01:20.267 --> 00:01:21.434
[shouting]

15
00:01:21.435 --> 00:01:22.895
- Fuck.
- [grunting]

16
00:01:23.938 --> 00:01:25.855
Except that time in Maidenpool.

17
00:01:25.856 --> 00:01:27.858
[thunder rumbling]

18
00:01:29.110 --> 00:01:31.195
It was the inn boy
ate the widow woman's pie.

19
00:01:32.947 --> 00:01:35.281
Not me. I told you.

20
00:01:35.282 --> 00:01:36.407
[rooster crowing]

21
00:01:36.408 --> 00:01:38.119
Why. you...
[grunting]

22
00:01:39.745 --> 00:01:40.913
[sniffing]

23
00:01:44.250 --> 00:01:45.709
Doesn't matter now.

24
00:01:47.628 --> 00:01:49.630
[thunder rumbling]

25
00:01:53.008 --> 00:01:55.010
[exhales sharply]

26
00:02:02.309 --> 00:02:04.644
I'd leave your sword. but it...

27
00:02:04.645 --> 00:02:06.272
it would only rust
in the ground.

28
00:02:08.816 --> 00:02:10.276
[sniffing]

29
00:02:11.652 --> 00:02:14.238
[sobbing]
I wish you didn't die. ser.

30
00:02:18.868 --> 00:02:20.785
[whimpering]

31
00:02:20.786 --> 00:02:22.621
I'll take good care
of the horses.

32
00:02:26.917 --> 00:02:29.002
[distant sheep bleating]

33
00:02:29.003 --> 00:02:30.421
[horse nickering]

34
00:02:32.089 --> 00:02:34.091
[birdsong]

35
00:02:37.678 --> 00:02:40.513
Eat like a king
if I sold you three.

36
00:02:40.514 --> 00:02:42.473
[horse neighing]

37
00:02:42.474 --> 00:02:44.226
For a year or two.

38
00:02:45.644 --> 00:02:47.646
- Then what?
- [horse neighing]

39
00:02:51.483 --> 00:02:54.236
That road ends in outlawry
or beggary.

40
00:02:55.905 --> 00:02:58.365
[wind whistling]

41
00:03:04.330 --> 00:03:06.080
We could go to a city.

42
00:03:06.081 --> 00:03:08.083
[horse nickering]

43
00:03:09.501 --> 00:03:11.753
King's Landing?
Lannisport?

44
00:03:11.754 --> 00:03:12.963
[horse huffing]

45
00:03:25.851 --> 00:03:27.143
Could join the City Watch.

46
00:03:27.144 --> 00:03:29.146
[horses snorting. nickering]

47
00:03:32.691 --> 00:03:34.193
Stop raping. ser.

48
00:03:39.698 --> 00:03:41.700
[horse neighing]

49
00:03:45.454 --> 00:03:47.581
Fits my grip
as well as it ever fit his.

50
00:03:48.624 --> 00:03:50.626
[wind intensifying]

51
00:03:53.128 --> 00:03:55.005
And there is a tourney
at Ashford Meadow.

52
00:04:02.888 --> 00:04:05.891
[♪ dramatic theme playing]

53
00:04:11.522 --> 00:04:13.565
- [wet splatting]
- [relieving sighs]

54
00:04:15.025 --> 00:04:17.027
[continues sighing]

55
00:04:23.158 --> 00:04:25.160
[bird chirping]

56
00:04:28.706 --> 00:04:30.708
[chirping continues]

57
00:04:33.627 --> 00:04:35.336
[grunting]

58
00:04:35.337 --> 00:04:38.340
[♪ melancholy music playing]

59
00:04:47.141 --> 00:04:49.351
[horse nickering]

60
00:05:16.754 --> 00:05:18.005
[dog barking]

61
00:05:23.635 --> 00:05:25.637
[crows cawing]

62
00:05:27.473 --> 00:05:29.850
Hello there.
Are you the stableboy?

63
00:05:34.688 --> 00:05:37.231
I want the palfrey rubbed down.

64
00:05:37.232 --> 00:05:39.734
And oats for all three.
You tend to them?

65
00:05:39.735 --> 00:05:42.653
I could. if I wanted.

66
00:05:42.654 --> 00:05:44.614
[Dunk] None of that.
See to the horses.

67
00:05:44.615 --> 00:05:47.076
You'll get a copper if you do well.
and a clout in the ear if not.

68
00:05:50.621 --> 00:05:52.623
[liquid bubbling]

69
00:05:54.333 --> 00:05:55.626
[door opens]

70
00:05:56.919 --> 00:05:57.920
[pots clanging]

71
00:05:58.670 --> 00:05:59.671
Sit where you like.

72
00:06:00.631 --> 00:06:02.633
[pots continue clanging]

73
00:06:12.059 --> 00:06:14.185
There's good lamb
roasted with a crust of herbs

74
00:06:14.186 --> 00:06:16.730
and some ducks my son shot down.
Which will you have?

75
00:06:18.065 --> 00:06:19.190
Both.

76
00:06:19.191 --> 00:06:21.401
[laughing]

77
00:06:21.402 --> 00:06:22.945
You're big enough for it.

78
00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:30.202
[chair scraping]

79
00:06:32.788 --> 00:06:33.831
[clears throat]

80
00:06:34.373 --> 00:06:36.708
- How much farther to Ashford?
- Day's ride.

81
00:06:39.044 --> 00:06:41.380
Is my boy seeing to your horses
or has he run off again?

82
00:06:42.548 --> 00:06:44.132
[sniffing]
No. he's there.

83
00:06:44.133 --> 00:06:45.925
Half the town's
gone down the tourney.

84
00:06:45.926 --> 00:06:47.635
Mine would. too.
if I allowed it.

85
00:06:47.636 --> 00:06:49.804
[chuckles] I swear.
I couldn't tell you why.

86
00:06:49.805 --> 00:06:52.015
Knights are built the same
as other men.

87
00:06:53.058 --> 00:06:55.769
And I never knew a joust
to change the price of eggs.

88
00:06:58.522 --> 00:07:00.690
Bound for the tourney yourself?

89
00:07:00.691 --> 00:07:02.109
[guest] I dreamed of you.

90
00:07:09.032 --> 00:07:11.743
Stay the fuck away from me.
You hear?

91
00:07:13.328 --> 00:07:14.371
My lord?

92
00:07:22.713 --> 00:07:23.714
[blows forcefully]

93
00:07:29.678 --> 00:07:31.680
- [heavy footfall]
- [stairs creaking]

94
00:07:36.560 --> 00:07:38.227
[coins jingling]

95
00:07:38.228 --> 00:07:39.729
Never you mind that one. ser.

96
00:07:39.730 --> 00:07:41.190
I'll see about your food.

97
00:07:45.444 --> 00:07:47.487
- [door closes]
- [dog barking]

98
00:07:47.488 --> 00:07:49.447
[horse whinnying]

99
00:07:49.448 --> 00:07:53.284
- [stableboy] Hiya! Take that! Yah!
- [horse neighing]

100
00:07:53.285 --> 00:07:56.996
[vocalizing]

101
00:07:56.997 --> 00:07:59.582
- Oi!
- [gasps] My lord.

102
00:07:59.583 --> 00:08:02.710
- You thief!
- I... I did not mean to offend you.

103
00:08:02.711 --> 00:08:05.171
Take that armor off you.
Now!

104
00:08:05.172 --> 00:08:08.716
And be glad Thunder didn't kick you
in that fool head of yours.

105
00:08:08.717 --> 00:08:10.551
He's a war horse.
not a boy's pony.

106
00:08:10.552 --> 00:08:12.345
I could ride him as well as you.

107
00:08:12.346 --> 00:08:14.515
- [horse huffing]
- Close your insolent mouth.

108
00:08:15.182 --> 00:08:16.016
I...

109
00:08:16.517 --> 00:08:18.559
I'm a knight.
I'll have you know.

110
00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:20.229
You don't look to be a knight.

111
00:08:21.313 --> 00:08:24.315
- What. all knights look the same. do they?
- No.

112
00:08:24.316 --> 00:08:26.193
But they don't look
like you either.

113
00:08:27.319 --> 00:08:28.612
Your belt's made of rope.

114
00:08:29.988 --> 00:08:32.573
So long as it holds
my scabbard. it serves.

115
00:08:32.574 --> 00:08:34.367
Are you going
to the tourney. then?

116
00:08:34.368 --> 00:08:35.953
Do you mean to enter the lists?

117
00:08:36.954 --> 00:08:38.329
Yeah. I suppose I do.

118
00:08:38.330 --> 00:08:41.332
Take me with you. ser.
Please.

119
00:08:41.333 --> 00:08:43.167
And what might
your mother say to that?

120
00:08:43.168 --> 00:08:44.544
Not much.

121
00:08:44.545 --> 00:08:45.962
- She's dead.
- [scoffs]

122
00:08:45.963 --> 00:08:47.839
Is the innkeeper not your...

123
00:08:50.634 --> 00:08:52.093
You're an orphan boy.

124
00:08:52.094 --> 00:08:53.095
Are you?

125
00:08:54.555 --> 00:08:56.431
I was. Once.

126
00:08:57.182 --> 00:08:59.393
Till my ser took me in.

127
00:09:00.936 --> 00:09:02.729
Taught me arms
and riding. and...

128
00:09:04.273 --> 00:09:06.400
and taught me everything. really.
[chuckles softly]

129
00:09:07.609 --> 00:09:09.527
- Best he could.
- [horse nickering]

130
00:09:09.528 --> 00:09:11.862
If you could bring me
to Ashford.

131
00:09:11.863 --> 00:09:13.239
I could squire for you. ser.

132
00:09:13.240 --> 00:09:15.992
- [sighs]
- And you can teach me best you can.

133
00:09:15.993 --> 00:09:18.160
No. I have no need
for a squire. lad.

134
00:09:18.161 --> 00:09:19.954
Every knight needs a squire.

135
00:09:19.955 --> 00:09:22.708
And you look like you need one
more than most.

136
00:09:25.419 --> 00:09:27.379
And you look like you need
a good clout in the ear.

137
00:09:28.755 --> 00:09:30.047
Fill me a sack of oats.

138
00:09:30.048 --> 00:09:32.259
I'm off for Ashford.
Alone.

139
00:09:38.432 --> 00:09:41.851
Look. lad. I promise you...

140
00:09:41.852 --> 00:09:44.187
you're better off not squiring
for the likes of me.

141
00:09:52.279 --> 00:09:53.488
- For your help.
- [coin pings]

142
00:09:54.781 --> 00:09:56.741
- [dog barking in distance]
- [Dunk scoffs]

143
00:09:56.742 --> 00:09:58.075
Sulk all you wish.

144
00:09:58.076 --> 00:10:00.036
I know you'll scoop it up
as soon as I'm gone.

145
00:10:00.037 --> 00:10:01.538
[horse nickering]

146
00:10:05.292 --> 00:10:08.295
[♪ soft music playing]

147
00:10:46.124 --> 00:10:48.668
- [horse neighing]
- [people chattering in distance]

148
00:10:48.669 --> 00:10:51.672
[♪ inspiring music playing]

149
00:10:59.846 --> 00:11:01.847
[people chattering]

150
00:11:01.848 --> 00:11:04.851
♪

151
00:11:41.388 --> 00:11:42.597
Sorry.

152
00:11:46.977 --> 00:11:49.729
[soldier speaking indistinctly]

153
00:11:49.730 --> 00:11:51.230
- Piss off.
- [soldiers laughing]

154
00:11:51.231 --> 00:11:52.482
Beg pardon. men.

155
00:11:54.359 --> 00:11:56.486
I wish to speak
to the master of the games.

156
00:12:00.782 --> 00:12:03.201
[children grunting]

157
00:12:04.745 --> 00:12:06.412
- [head thuds]
- Oh!

158
00:12:06.413 --> 00:12:08.665
- [children continue playing]
- What do you want. man?

159
00:12:10.292 --> 00:12:11.584
[child] Got you again!

160
00:12:11.585 --> 00:12:14.045
I. uh. came for the tourney.

161
00:12:15.213 --> 00:12:18.090
My lord's tourney
is a contest for knights.

162
00:12:18.091 --> 00:12:19.550
- You a knight?
- Hyah!

163
00:12:19.551 --> 00:12:21.595
Oi! Psst!

164
00:12:25.724 --> 00:12:27.058
A knight with a name. mayhaps?

165
00:12:27.851 --> 00:12:29.644
Uh. Dunk.

166
00:12:31.146 --> 00:12:33.689
Ser Dunk.

167
00:12:33.690 --> 00:12:37.486
I... I was squire to Ser Arlan of Pennytree
since I was a boy.

168
00:12:38.570 --> 00:12:41.782
He knighted me before he passed.
with his own sword.

169
00:12:45.911 --> 00:12:48.121
That's his penny there
in the hilt.

170
00:12:50.499 --> 00:12:53.001
Well. a sword it is
for a certainty.

171
00:12:54.211 --> 00:12:56.170
But I've never heard
of this Arlan of Pennytree.

172
00:12:56.171 --> 00:12:57.546
You were his squire. you say?

173
00:12:57.547 --> 00:12:59.966
He always meant for me
to be a knight one day...

174
00:13:01.134 --> 00:13:02.177
as he was.

175
00:13:03.178 --> 00:13:04.888
Am I to be a knight
one day. ser?

176
00:13:05.931 --> 00:13:08.224
- As you are?
- [sheep bleating]

177
00:13:08.225 --> 00:13:09.392
[spitting]

178
00:13:12.354 --> 00:13:15.147
When he was dying.
he called for his longsword

179
00:13:15.148 --> 00:13:16.399
and bade me kneel.

180
00:13:17.734 --> 00:13:19.236
Charged me to be a good knight.

181
00:13:20.153 --> 00:13:22.030
- [insect buzzing]
- To defend the weak and the innocent.

182
00:13:23.573 --> 00:13:25.574
Serve the realm
with all my might.

183
00:13:25.575 --> 00:13:27.159
And I swore that I would.

184
00:13:27.160 --> 00:13:29.162
[snorting. hocking loudly]

185
00:13:30.539 --> 00:13:31.581
[spitting]

186
00:13:32.666 --> 00:13:35.125
Any knight can make a knight.
it's true.

187
00:13:35.126 --> 00:13:38.296
Were there witnesses
to your dubbing?

188
00:13:38.880 --> 00:13:41.383
Only a robin in a thorn tree.
[chuckles]

189
00:13:44.636 --> 00:13:46.263
This is Ashford town. lad.

190
00:13:47.597 --> 00:13:50.559
Know what comes to men here
who pretend at sacred oaths?

191
00:13:51.101 --> 00:13:52.810
- I'm... I'm not...
- We hang you

192
00:13:52.811 --> 00:13:55.313
naked by your hands
and your feet...

193
00:13:56.314 --> 00:13:59.817
lower you down asshole first
onto a sharpened point

194
00:13:59.818 --> 00:14:01.361
and fuck you dry.

195
00:14:02.112 --> 00:14:05.406
Call it the Ashford chair.
So. I ask you again.

196
00:14:05.407 --> 00:14:06.907
Were there witnesses
to your dubbing

197
00:14:06.908 --> 00:14:08.743
besides a fuckin' songbird?

198
00:14:10.161 --> 00:14:14.623
Well. the...
see. it was raining.

199
00:14:14.624 --> 00:14:17.210
- Uh...
- I'm bullshitting you.

200
00:14:17.752 --> 00:14:18.753
[laughing]

201
00:14:20.213 --> 00:14:21.755
[chuckles nervously]

202
00:14:21.756 --> 00:14:23.008
"Ashford chair."

203
00:14:24.050 --> 00:14:25.551
You take a boot to the head?

204
00:14:25.552 --> 00:14:27.636
This is the Reach.
not the Riverlands.

205
00:14:27.637 --> 00:14:29.763
- "Ashford chair." [chuckles]
- Think we're fending off

206
00:14:29.764 --> 00:14:31.682
some scourge of cottagers.
scuttling about.

207
00:14:31.683 --> 00:14:33.267
entering tourneys?

208
00:14:33.268 --> 00:14:36.061
[snorting. hocking loudly]

209
00:14:36.062 --> 00:14:38.981
You'd need coin.
[spitting] Armor.

210
00:14:38.982 --> 00:14:40.482
Horses. Men.

211
00:14:40.483 --> 00:14:43.068
Training. gods be good.

212
00:14:43.069 --> 00:14:44.904
Imagine the poor farmer
charging down

213
00:14:44.905 --> 00:14:46.739
Lyonel Baratheon in the lists.

214
00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:48.240
Mm. that would be...

215
00:14:48.241 --> 00:14:49.783
A different sort
of entertainment.

216
00:14:49.784 --> 00:14:52.745
Mm. Well. I'm no farmer.

217
00:14:52.746 --> 00:14:54.289
Yet you've come dressed as one.

218
00:14:57.208 --> 00:15:00.252
Look. man. my Lord Ashford

219
00:15:00.253 --> 00:15:03.631
fancies himself of great import.
Gods know why.

220
00:15:03.632 --> 00:15:06.091
Well. that means I'm to ward off
every landed knight

221
00:15:06.092 --> 00:15:07.927
and sellsword
vying to challenge.

222
00:15:07.928 --> 00:15:10.221
You understand?
There are princes about.

223
00:15:12.098 --> 00:15:13.308
No. of course.

224
00:15:15.936 --> 00:15:17.938
[swords clanging in distance]

225
00:15:21.816 --> 00:15:22.943
Your late master.

226
00:15:25.654 --> 00:15:27.781
He'll be known to the true knights
here assembled?

227
00:15:28.907 --> 00:15:31.033
There was a pavilion

228
00:15:31.034 --> 00:15:33.035
flying the banner
of House Dondarrion.

229
00:15:33.036 --> 00:15:34.954
Aye. Ser Manfred of that house.

230
00:15:34.955 --> 00:15:36.705
Ser Arlan served
his lord father in Dorne

231
00:15:36.706 --> 00:15:38.040
a few years past.

232
00:15:38.041 --> 00:15:39.708
Ser Manfred will remember us.

233
00:15:39.709 --> 00:15:42.002
By scent alone. no doubt.

234
00:15:42.003 --> 00:15:44.546
If he'll speak to your good honor.
bring him here with you

235
00:15:44.547 --> 00:15:46.256
before the tourney
begins on the morrow.

236
00:15:46.257 --> 00:15:47.132
Leave your escorts behind.

237
00:15:47.133 --> 00:15:48.676
[insects buzzing]

238
00:15:48.677 --> 00:15:50.303
- As you say.
- Aye.

239
00:15:53.139 --> 00:15:55.849
You are aware that those
vanquished in tourney

240
00:15:55.850 --> 00:15:57.643
forfeit their arms.
armor. and horse

241
00:15:57.644 --> 00:15:59.478
to the victors.
and must ransom them back?

242
00:15:59.479 --> 00:16:01.522
- Aye.
- And you have coin

243
00:16:01.523 --> 00:16:04.817
- to pay such ransom?
- Oh. gods. no.

244
00:16:04.818 --> 00:16:07.737
I... I mean.
I won't have need of coin.

245
00:16:10.740 --> 00:16:12.866
- [thud]
- [groaning]

246
00:16:12.867 --> 00:16:14.118
Seven fu...

247
00:16:14.119 --> 00:16:16.120
[horse neighing]

248
00:16:16.121 --> 00:16:18.122
[♪ fiddle playing faintly]

249
00:16:18.123 --> 00:16:20.125
[people chattering]

250
00:16:26.381 --> 00:16:28.383
[chatter and laughter]

251
00:16:35.432 --> 00:16:37.350
- Mind those two. Good girl.
- [horse nickering]

252
00:16:38.351 --> 00:16:40.353
[chatter. laughter continue]

253
00:16:42.564 --> 00:16:43.772
Uh. pardon. sers.

254
00:16:43.773 --> 00:16:45.357
I... I need speak
with Ser Manfred.

255
00:16:45.358 --> 00:16:46.567
[lordling] [belching]
Good.

256
00:16:46.568 --> 00:16:49.612
He's napping. ser.
Wake him for a stag.

257
00:16:50.405 --> 00:16:51.865
I. uh... [clearing throat]

258
00:16:52.866 --> 00:16:54.450
I don't...
I don't have a stag.

259
00:16:54.451 --> 00:16:56.493
What kind of knight
don't got a stag?

260
00:16:56.494 --> 00:16:58.871
- It's a hedge knight. ain't it?
- What?

261
00:16:58.872 --> 00:17:01.123
It's like a knight. but sadder.

262
00:17:01.124 --> 00:17:02.750
No. I'm... I'm not sad...

263
00:17:02.751 --> 00:17:05.044
He's gotta sleep in the hedges
'cause no lord'll have it.

264
00:17:05.045 --> 00:17:07.297
Aw. That is sad.

265
00:17:08.006 --> 00:17:10.215
And Ser Manfred's
fucked its wife. too.

266
00:17:10.216 --> 00:17:13.260
- No. I... I don't have a wife.
- Oh!

267
00:17:13.261 --> 00:17:15.220
'Cause we're used
to husbands coming 'round.

268
00:17:15.221 --> 00:17:16.847
Likes fucking wives. that one.

269
00:17:16.848 --> 00:17:18.599
Near as much
as he likes fucking us.

270
00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:21.518
Told me he's on a mission
to turn the whole world red.

271
00:17:21.519 --> 00:17:24.480
- Well. we're already red.
- So we are.

272
00:17:24.481 --> 00:17:27.066
[both laughing]

273
00:17:27.067 --> 00:17:31.529
Well. um. when do you expect
Ser Manfred to wake. then?

274
00:17:32.489 --> 00:17:34.782
It might wanna try back
at evenfall.

275
00:17:34.783 --> 00:17:36.159
Evenfall.

276
00:17:39.204 --> 00:17:40.872
- Goodbye.
- Yeah. [clearing throat]

277
00:17:41.998 --> 00:17:44.750
- Arse.
- [girls laughing]

278
00:17:44.751 --> 00:17:46.753
[knights shouting]

279
00:17:47.879 --> 00:17:50.465
- [horse nickering]
- Why'd she say that. huh?

280
00:17:52.550 --> 00:17:53.718
We're not sad.

281
00:17:55.553 --> 00:17:57.179
[horse neighing]

282
00:17:57.180 --> 00:17:59.890
Certainly not rising-to-the-level-
of-a-comment sad.

283
00:17:59.891 --> 00:18:01.225
[horse nickering]

284
00:18:01.226 --> 00:18:03.478
Besides. Ser Arlan
always said that...

285
00:18:04.646 --> 00:18:06.898
a hedge knight
was the truest kind of knight.

286
00:18:08.900 --> 00:18:11.777
When we win our first tilt.
we'll have the loser's armor

287
00:18:11.778 --> 00:18:14.071
- and horse. or his gold.
- [horse nickering]

288
00:18:14.072 --> 00:18:16.031
- [knights shouting]
- Won't be sad then.

289
00:18:16.032 --> 00:18:18.034
[grunting]

290
00:18:19.619 --> 00:18:21.287
[horse neighing]

291
00:18:22.872 --> 00:18:25.500
I know.
Said if we <i>did</i> win.

292
00:18:27.085 --> 00:18:28.502
Look. it's not a crime
against the king

293
00:18:28.503 --> 00:18:30.212
to enjoy a nice thought
for a trice.

294
00:18:30.213 --> 00:18:31.964
[grunting]

295
00:18:31.965 --> 00:18:34.551
- [horse neighing]
- Do not muck about with me. Raymun.

296
00:18:35.093 --> 00:18:38.054
- [groaning]
- You're a good-for-nothing useless rat.

297
00:18:42.934 --> 00:18:43.977
[grunting]

298
00:18:49.190 --> 00:18:50.942
What are you gawping at.
you blue-eyed cunt?

299
00:18:54.154 --> 00:18:55.822
That's a longsword you wear?

300
00:18:58.366 --> 00:19:00.034
Uh. yes. it is mine by right.

301
00:19:00.577 --> 00:19:02.078
That's an odd thing to say.

302
00:19:05.206 --> 00:19:07.207
I'm Ser Steffon Fossoway.

303
00:19:07.208 --> 00:19:08.334
Come try me.

304
00:19:09.419 --> 00:19:12.004
As you see. me cousin here
is not ripe yet.

305
00:19:12.005 --> 00:19:13.755
Do it. ser.

306
00:19:13.756 --> 00:19:16.633
I may not be ripe. but my cousin's
rotten to the core.

307
00:19:16.634 --> 00:19:18.344
- Knock the seeds out of him.
- Quiet!

308
00:19:21.306 --> 00:19:24.516
I... I thank you.
but I have matters to attend.

309
00:19:24.517 --> 00:19:26.977
What. matters of the hedge.
I have no doubt.

310
00:19:26.978 --> 00:19:29.396
[laughing]

311
00:19:29.397 --> 00:19:31.398
Fucking size of ya.

312
00:19:31.399 --> 00:19:33.275
Stupid bastard.

313
00:19:33.276 --> 00:19:34.527
Ser Grance!

314
00:19:40.491 --> 00:19:42.951
Perhaps we should seek
quieter accommodations.

315
00:19:42.952 --> 00:19:44.954
[horse grunting]

316
00:19:46.331 --> 00:19:49.334
[♪ joyful whistling music
playing]

317
00:19:52.795 --> 00:19:54.255
[insect buzzing]

318
00:20:05.516 --> 00:20:07.518
[insects continue buzzing]

319
00:20:09.312 --> 00:20:12.315
♪

320
00:20:26.955 --> 00:20:28.957
[horses nickering]

321
00:20:31.834 --> 00:20:34.628
[sniffing]
Oh. Fuck.

322
00:20:34.629 --> 00:20:36.214
[grunting]

323
00:20:38.132 --> 00:20:39.467
[sniffing]

324
00:20:49.102 --> 00:20:50.686
[people chattering]

325
00:20:50.687 --> 00:20:52.021
He's napping still.

326
00:20:53.064 --> 00:20:54.606
- Still?
- Mm.

327
00:20:54.607 --> 00:20:56.901
On account of his gouty toes.

328
00:20:58.528 --> 00:21:02.406
One of life's absurd
little miseries. to be sure.

329
00:21:02.407 --> 00:21:04.157
[Dunk sighs]

330
00:21:04.158 --> 00:21:06.994
Makes for restless nights.
The poor dear.

331
00:21:06.995 --> 00:21:08.829
Right. absolutely.
It's just... [sighs]

332
00:21:08.830 --> 00:21:10.956
Well. it is of some urgency
that I speak with him.

333
00:21:10.957 --> 00:21:13.835
so I may enter
the lists on the morrow.

334
00:21:15.044 --> 00:21:18.130
- What's this?
- It means the joust.

335
00:21:18.131 --> 00:21:19.756
Awful dangerous. that.

336
00:21:19.757 --> 00:21:22.050
- Yes. well. um...
- [water pouring]

337
00:21:22.051 --> 00:21:24.721
I'm not troubled
with a wealth of options. am I?

338
00:21:25.847 --> 00:21:27.472
And if I mean
to take service in a castle...

339
00:21:27.473 --> 00:21:30.434
It must put its body at hazard
for the pleasure of strangers.

340
00:21:30.435 --> 00:21:31.685
Ain't that our job?

341
00:21:31.686 --> 00:21:33.937
- [gasps]
- Ah! Shut up!

342
00:21:33.938 --> 00:21:35.898
- You're meant to be dead.
- [sighs]

343
00:21:36.858 --> 00:21:39.609
Find a safer trade. lad.
You'll be happier for it.

344
00:21:39.610 --> 00:21:41.946
One whore to another.

345
00:21:42.905 --> 00:21:44.741
[both laughing]

346
00:21:46.534 --> 00:21:47.910
Must you mock me?

347
00:21:48.870 --> 00:21:50.413
I was only asking
for a bit of help.

348
00:21:51.497 --> 00:21:53.583
I'll try Ser Manfred
back in the morning.

349
00:21:55.460 --> 00:21:56.626
Sorry. lad.

350
00:21:56.627 --> 00:21:58.003
[Beony] Aye.

351
00:21:58.004 --> 00:21:59.421
We don't mean to mock you.

352
00:21:59.422 --> 00:22:02.591
- We see plenty of green boys every tourney.
- Mm.

353
00:22:02.592 --> 00:22:05.344
All with glory in their minds.
but never in their hands.

354
00:22:05.345 --> 00:22:08.348
Well. perhaps
I will be different.

355
00:22:10.767 --> 00:22:13.435
Be good to your body. knight.

356
00:22:13.436 --> 00:22:14.896
Last one you're like to have.

357
00:22:19.984 --> 00:22:23.278
- [♪ lively strings playing]
- [people chattering]

358
00:22:23.279 --> 00:22:25.822
[performer]
<i>Our brave hero forges on.</i>

359
00:22:25.823 --> 00:22:28.867
<i>leaving all he knows behind.</i>

360
00:22:28.868 --> 00:22:33.288
<i>A father and a friend.
may seem the world unkind.</i>

361
00:22:33.289 --> 00:22:34.706
[distant cheering and applause]

362
00:22:34.707 --> 00:22:37.125
<i>Fate has set his lonely path</i>

363
00:22:37.126 --> 00:22:38.795
<i>through corridors of chance.</i>

364
00:22:39.712 --> 00:22:44.591
A boy from nothing risks it all.
ignoring looks askance.

365
00:22:44.592 --> 00:22:47.260
- Perhaps he's only stupid...
- [actor whooshing]

366
00:22:47.261 --> 00:22:49.429
...holding fast
his mirror shield.

367
00:22:49.430 --> 00:22:55.352
Great honor his ambition.
must keep a truth concealed.

368
00:22:55.353 --> 00:22:57.729
For if his humble shape
is bared.

369
00:22:57.730 --> 00:22:59.899
a foul and fiery demise.

370
00:23:00.400 --> 00:23:02.150
Should the dragon discover

371
00:23:02.151 --> 00:23:04.986
none but a man
in great disguise.

372
00:23:04.987 --> 00:23:07.948
[dragon screeching]

373
00:23:07.949 --> 00:23:09.574
[audience gasping]

374
00:23:09.575 --> 00:23:11.577
[cheering and applause]

375
00:23:16.999 --> 00:23:19.001
[cheering and applause continue]

376
00:23:31.514 --> 00:23:33.516
[people chattering]

377
00:23:36.936 --> 00:23:39.604
- [fire whooshing]
- [people cheering]

378
00:23:39.605 --> 00:23:41.607
Halfman! Halfman!

379
00:23:43.484 --> 00:23:45.318
Do I look like
a half man to you?

380
00:23:45.319 --> 00:23:48.113
Aye.
Half man. half giant.

381
00:23:48.114 --> 00:23:49.656
Look. I'm sorry.

382
00:23:49.657 --> 00:23:51.783
I should not have urged you
to try my cousin.

383
00:23:51.784 --> 00:23:55.120
He'd have broken your hand
or a knee. if he could.

384
00:23:55.121 --> 00:23:57.038
He likes to batter men
in the yard.

385
00:23:57.039 --> 00:23:59.083
you know. in case
he meets them in the lists.

386
00:24:01.002 --> 00:24:02.502
He did not break you.

387
00:24:02.503 --> 00:24:04.088
[scoffs]
I'm his blood.

388
00:24:04.922 --> 00:24:07.090
Though he is the senior branch
of the apple tree.

389
00:24:07.091 --> 00:24:08.759
which he never ceases
to remind me.

390
00:24:10.511 --> 00:24:12.929
Will you and your cousin
ride in the tourney?

391
00:24:12.930 --> 00:24:15.015
He will.
I would that I could.

392
00:24:15.016 --> 00:24:17.101
but I'm only a squire.

393
00:24:21.147 --> 00:24:22.773
Fight well for a squire.

394
00:24:24.233 --> 00:24:26.067
You have the look
of a challenger.

395
00:24:26.068 --> 00:24:27.904
Whose shield
do you mean to strike?

396
00:24:30.740 --> 00:24:32.574
Makes no difference.

397
00:24:32.575 --> 00:24:34.327
[laughing] That's what
you're supposed to say.

398
00:24:39.207 --> 00:24:41.374
Though it makes all the difference
in the world.

399
00:24:41.375 --> 00:24:42.543
[chuckles]

400
00:24:44.504 --> 00:24:45.505
You hungry?

401
00:24:46.881 --> 00:24:48.007
Always.

402
00:24:49.050 --> 00:24:52.053
[♪ mysterious. percussive
music playing]

403
00:24:55.598 --> 00:24:57.600
[people chattering]

404
00:24:59.310 --> 00:25:01.811
[knights shouting indistinctly]

405
00:25:01.812 --> 00:25:04.815
[music and chatter continue]

406
00:25:08.861 --> 00:25:11.280
[knight laughing]

407
00:25:12.114 --> 00:25:15.034
Lyonel Baratheon.
The Laughing Storm. they call him.

408
00:25:16.953 --> 00:25:18.495
I thought he'd be bigger.

409
00:25:18.496 --> 00:25:20.748
[Lyonel Baratheon]
Four thousand years ago...

410
00:25:21.999 --> 00:25:24.209
- Four thousand years...
- Where are you going?

411
00:25:24.210 --> 00:25:27.546
...ago... cunts.
I can't hear myself.

412
00:25:27.547 --> 00:25:32.592
I've had a profound thought.
if anyone would care to listen.

413
00:25:32.593 --> 00:25:33.970
- [room quiets]
- [table banging]

414
00:25:36.305 --> 00:25:38.723
Four thousand years ago.

415
00:25:38.724 --> 00:25:41.726
our ancestors
gathered in that...

416
00:25:41.727 --> 00:25:44.437
[clearing throat]
...big field outside

417
00:25:44.438 --> 00:25:46.648
to blood each other with sticks

418
00:25:46.649 --> 00:25:48.942
and have a little bit
of gay fun.

419
00:25:48.943 --> 00:25:52.571
And they say it was
this country's first-ever joust.

420
00:25:52.572 --> 00:25:54.115
Well. I say...

421
00:26:00.496 --> 00:26:02.038
Uh. the fuck was I gonna say?

422
00:26:02.039 --> 00:26:03.958
[muttering]
"First-ever joust..."

423
00:26:05.585 --> 00:26:06.586
Ah.

424
00:26:09.672 --> 00:26:12.842
Men could not have devised
such a joy.

425
00:26:15.886 --> 00:26:17.053
So. who was it?

426
00:26:17.054 --> 00:26:19.098
[sipping loudly]

427
00:26:20.641 --> 00:26:21.684
[Lyonel] Huh?

428
00:26:22.727 --> 00:26:23.769
Who was it?

429
00:26:25.688 --> 00:26:27.856
[person coughing]

430
00:26:27.857 --> 00:26:29.107
Mm.

431
00:26:29.108 --> 00:26:31.110
[laughing]

432
00:26:32.945 --> 00:26:34.904
[sighs]
Fuck it.

433
00:26:34.905 --> 00:26:36.448
A hundred gold
to the man. beast.

434
00:26:36.449 --> 00:26:38.033
or god who sticks me best.

435
00:26:38.034 --> 00:26:39.492
- [all cheering]
- [mugs pounding]

436
00:26:39.493 --> 00:26:43.038
Now. eat your birds
so we can dance!

437
00:26:43.039 --> 00:26:46.042
- [drums beating]
- [guests chattering]

438
00:26:51.172 --> 00:26:54.175
- [♪ string music playing]
- [guests shouting. cheering]

439
00:26:59.013 --> 00:27:01.598
[music and shouting continue]

440
00:27:01.599 --> 00:27:03.601
[clapping in rhythm]

441
00:27:23.329 --> 00:27:25.039
[mouthing silently]

442
00:27:30.878 --> 00:27:32.880
[music and clapping continue]

443
00:27:42.264 --> 00:27:43.516
[Lyonel sighs]

444
00:27:44.767 --> 00:27:47.978
You ever been punched
in the face before?

445
00:27:50.189 --> 00:27:51.940
I beg... I beg your pardon.
Ser Lyonel?

446
00:27:51.941 --> 00:27:55.026
Big men get punched
more than little men.

447
00:27:55.027 --> 00:27:56.237
Did you know that?

448
00:27:57.697 --> 00:27:59.990
No. but... but I believe it.

449
00:28:02.702 --> 00:28:05.912
That why you slouch?
So you don't get punched?

450
00:28:05.913 --> 00:28:08.289
I... I don't slouch.

451
00:28:08.290 --> 00:28:10.375
Oh. you've been
cowering all evening

452
00:28:10.376 --> 00:28:12.919
like a maiden
on her wedding night.

453
00:28:12.920 --> 00:28:14.796
[chuckles]

454
00:28:14.797 --> 00:28:18.216
I... I meant
no disrespect. ser. honest.

455
00:28:18.217 --> 00:28:21.804
Where I grew up. you...
you learn to go unnoticed. is all.

456
00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.473
The seven above
gave you tallness.

457
00:28:25.474 --> 00:28:26.726
So. be tall.

458
00:28:28.144 --> 00:28:30.896
Or I will name you a heretic
and burn you.

459
00:28:31.981 --> 00:28:35.859
Drown you.
Drop you off a tall pl...

460
00:28:35.860 --> 00:28:37.777
I don't know.
W-What do they do to heretics?

461
00:28:37.778 --> 00:28:40.321
Burn them. my lord.

462
00:28:40.322 --> 00:28:42.073
- Fine.
- [blade clatters]

463
00:28:42.074 --> 00:28:43.617
What have you brought me?

464
00:28:45.703 --> 00:28:46.704
Um...

465
00:28:48.998 --> 00:28:52.167
Uh. ser. I... [clearing throat]
beggin' your pardons.

466
00:28:52.168 --> 00:28:53.753
I... I didn't realize.

467
00:28:54.962 --> 00:28:57.006
You wish to curry my favor some.

468
00:28:58.466 --> 00:29:00.092
Yet you come with an empty hand.

469
00:29:04.680 --> 00:29:06.139
Lord Cafferen.

470
00:29:06.140 --> 00:29:08.057
the smug cunt in red...

471
00:29:08.058 --> 00:29:09.476
[cheering. laughter]

472
00:29:09.477 --> 00:29:11.644
...he is scarce
to pay his rents.

473
00:29:11.645 --> 00:29:13.730
His people starve each winter.

474
00:29:13.731 --> 00:29:16.108
yet even he shinied up this...

475
00:29:17.526 --> 00:29:19.444
bauble from
his family's cellars.

476
00:29:19.445 --> 00:29:22.447
for he understands
that all men. in their way.

477
00:29:22.448 --> 00:29:25.951
wish only for your help.
or your head.

478
00:29:28.913 --> 00:29:30.539
You've come for my head. then.

479
00:29:32.124 --> 00:29:33.750
W-What?

480
00:29:33.751 --> 00:29:36.169
No! No.

481
00:29:36.170 --> 00:29:40.424
Then. why the fuck
are you in my tent?

482
00:29:45.179 --> 00:29:46.680
S-Supper.

483
00:29:53.562 --> 00:29:55.230
[Lyonel laughing]

484
00:29:55.231 --> 00:29:57.233
[laughter]

485
00:29:59.276 --> 00:30:00.694
[chuckles] Alright.

486
00:30:02.905 --> 00:30:04.614
Actually makes sense.

487
00:30:04.615 --> 00:30:06.951
- Supper.
- What is your name. man?

488
00:30:08.786 --> 00:30:10.119
Dunk... Ser Dunk.

489
00:30:10.120 --> 00:30:11.539
That's ridiculous.

490
00:30:14.834 --> 00:30:16.668
[Lyonel clearing throat]

491
00:30:16.669 --> 00:30:18.044
Do you like dancing?

492
00:30:18.045 --> 00:30:20.005
- [guests stomping rhythmically]
- Doesn't everyone?

493
00:30:21.423 --> 00:30:24.467
- [♪ upbeat music playing]
- [chanting] Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

494
00:30:24.468 --> 00:30:26.470
[chanting and music continue]

495
00:30:35.521 --> 00:30:37.523
[exclaiming]

496
00:30:45.364 --> 00:30:46.574
- [stomping]
- [Dunk grunting]

497
00:31:04.842 --> 00:31:06.844
- [shouting]
- [guests cheering]

498
00:31:13.434 --> 00:31:16.269
- [♪ music continues playing]
- [laughing]

499
00:31:16.270 --> 00:31:18.272
[Lyonel cheering and exclaiming]

500
00:31:44.340 --> 00:31:45.924
[music ends abruptly]

501
00:31:45.925 --> 00:31:49.428
The swells heaved.
You could lick salt from the air.

502
00:31:51.138 --> 00:31:54.308
But I'd come to find what men do
when they die at sea.

503
00:31:56.060 --> 00:31:59.063
So. drove I on into the storm.

504
00:32:00.064 --> 00:32:02.066
[laughing]

505
00:32:03.734 --> 00:32:06.487
- Weren't you afraid?
- Ahh.

506
00:32:09.949 --> 00:32:11.992
Within every man.
there are many men.

507
00:32:13.786 --> 00:32:15.286
Mm.

508
00:32:15.287 --> 00:32:19.040
But that I had to do.
Stormlanders had always done.

509
00:32:19.041 --> 00:32:22.086
And if they had done it.
I could do it. too.

510
00:32:23.295 --> 00:32:24.296
Hm.

511
00:32:25.214 --> 00:32:27.049
You know. it's best
not to agonize.

512
00:32:30.427 --> 00:32:33.430
Yeah. I... I agonize a lot.

513
00:32:34.431 --> 00:32:35.807
[Lyonel] Mm.

514
00:32:35.808 --> 00:32:38.893
Sometimes. I... I think
I agonize too much.

515
00:32:38.894 --> 00:32:41.355
and I just end up
agonizing over that. [chuckles]

516
00:32:42.398 --> 00:32:43.815
Mm.

517
00:32:43.816 --> 00:32:46.985
And I'm quick and strong. sure.

518
00:32:46.986 --> 00:32:49.153
- Sure.
- But so are you.

519
00:32:49.154 --> 00:32:50.697
Sure.

520
00:32:50.698 --> 00:32:53.199
Plus. you've trained
sword and lance

521
00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:55.618
with the finest
masters-at-arms in the realm.

522
00:32:55.619 --> 00:32:56.704
I mean...

523
00:32:57.746 --> 00:33:00.666
what chance do I have?
Truly?

524
00:33:01.834 --> 00:33:04.378
Oh. you have no chance.
[chuckles]

525
00:33:06.088 --> 00:33:07.256
[Dunk sighs]

526
00:33:09.883 --> 00:33:14.179
But it's a great honor to test
oneself against a worthy foe.

527
00:33:16.473 --> 00:33:19.392
- No disrespect. ser.
- Mm.

528
00:33:19.393 --> 00:33:20.935
That's easy for you to say.

529
00:33:20.936 --> 00:33:24.439
You have a name. an inheritance.

530
00:33:24.440 --> 00:33:28.317
One loss. and I won't be able
to ransom back my own horse.

531
00:33:28.318 --> 00:33:30.570
[laughing]

532
00:33:30.571 --> 00:33:32.196
[chuckles softly]

533
00:33:32.197 --> 00:33:34.199
[both laughing]

534
00:33:35.284 --> 00:33:37.536
A knight without a horse
is no knight at all.

535
00:33:38.412 --> 00:33:40.414
- Aye.
- Mm.

536
00:33:41.665 --> 00:33:44.000
- [mug scraping]
- [Lyonel sipping loudly]

537
00:33:44.001 --> 00:33:45.210
So. what should I do?

538
00:33:49.715 --> 00:33:51.133
I don't know.

539
00:33:54.011 --> 00:33:55.721
I'm really quite drunk.

540
00:34:00.225 --> 00:34:02.227
[stomping. grunting]

541
00:34:04.146 --> 00:34:05.147
Okay.

542
00:34:06.231 --> 00:34:07.232
Thanks.

543
00:34:07.983 --> 00:34:08.984
[sighs]

544
00:34:09.735 --> 00:34:11.820
[hiccuping]
Sorry.

545
00:34:12.821 --> 00:34:13.989
[Dunk sniffing]

546
00:34:15.949 --> 00:34:17.117
[sighs]

547
00:34:18.744 --> 00:34:21.204
[guests chattering. laughing]

548
00:34:21.205 --> 00:34:22.455
[Dunk coughs]

549
00:34:22.456 --> 00:34:24.248
[couple laughing]

550
00:34:24.249 --> 00:34:26.502
[Manfred Dondarrion chuckling]

551
00:34:27.753 --> 00:34:29.630
[companions giggling]

552
00:34:30.631 --> 00:34:32.633
[all giggling]

553
00:34:34.051 --> 00:34:35.636
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

554
00:34:36.762 --> 00:34:38.805
He... he served your Lord Father

555
00:34:38.806 --> 00:34:40.849
to hunt the Vulture King
in the Red Mountains.

556
00:34:41.642 --> 00:34:42.850
I... I was only a boy. but...

557
00:34:42.851 --> 00:34:44.353
I thought you said
you were a Dornishman.

558
00:34:45.437 --> 00:34:47.772
No. he said he's hung
like a Dornishman.

559
00:34:47.773 --> 00:34:50.442
No. I said I've hung Dornishmen.

560
00:34:52.945 --> 00:34:54.779
Perhaps we would speak
on the morn.

561
00:34:54.780 --> 00:34:56.531
I know your penny knight not.

562
00:34:56.532 --> 00:34:59.075
Nor you. brother.
Be gone.

563
00:34:59.076 --> 00:35:00.369
[chuckles]

564
00:35:03.163 --> 00:35:06.290
But Ser Arlan took a wound
in your father's service.

565
00:35:06.291 --> 00:35:07.708
How could you have
forgotten him?

566
00:35:07.709 --> 00:35:09.043
- [soldiers shouting]
- [swords clanging]

567
00:35:09.044 --> 00:35:10.628
- [flesh squelching]
- [screaming]

568
00:35:10.629 --> 00:35:13.923
My lord father took 800 swords
into those mountains.

569
00:35:13.924 --> 00:35:17.219
We've forgotten men who reaped
much more than a wound.

570
00:35:17.970 --> 00:35:20.930
Please. ser. I... I will not
be allowed to challenge

571
00:35:20.931 --> 00:35:23.392
unless a knight
or a lord will vouch for me.

572
00:35:23.809 --> 00:35:24.643
And what is that to me?

573
00:35:26.520 --> 00:35:28.522
[chuckling]

574
00:35:36.363 --> 00:35:39.741
- [insects chirring]
- [cheering in distance]

575
00:35:51.044 --> 00:35:52.171
You!

576
00:35:53.672 --> 00:35:54.673
What...

577
00:35:56.008 --> 00:35:58.342
- [horse nickering]
- What are you doing?

578
00:35:58.343 --> 00:36:01.220
Cooking a fish.
Do you want some?

579
00:36:01.221 --> 00:36:04.557
No. I mean.
how did you get here?

580
00:36:04.558 --> 00:36:06.017
Did you steal a horse?

581
00:36:06.018 --> 00:36:07.852
I rode in the back
of a lamb cart.

582
00:36:07.853 --> 00:36:10.105
[scoffs]
Lamb cart.

583
00:36:11.732 --> 00:36:14.233
- Well. you best find another one.
- You can't make me go.

584
00:36:14.234 --> 00:36:16.110
I'd had enough of that inn.

585
00:36:16.111 --> 00:36:19.572
Now. listen. I'll have no more
insolence from you. boy.

586
00:36:19.573 --> 00:36:22.283
I should throw you over my horse
and take you home.

587
00:36:22.284 --> 00:36:24.827
You'd need to ride all the way
to King's Landing.

588
00:36:24.828 --> 00:36:27.289
- You'd miss the tourney.
- King's Landing?

589
00:36:28.290 --> 00:36:30.209
- You're from Flea Bottom?
- No.

590
00:36:31.960 --> 00:36:32.961
Aye.

591
00:36:40.636 --> 00:36:42.136
What are those doing there?

592
00:36:42.137 --> 00:36:44.347
I washed them.
I made the fire.

593
00:36:44.348 --> 00:36:46.682
caught the fish.
and groomed the horses.

594
00:36:46.683 --> 00:36:48.559
I would have raised
your pavilion.

595
00:36:48.560 --> 00:36:49.853
but I couldn't find one.

596
00:36:51.063 --> 00:36:53.439
- There's my pavilion.
- That's a tree.

597
00:36:53.440 --> 00:36:56.026
Yes. and it's all the pavilion
a true knight needs.

598
00:36:57.027 --> 00:36:59.905
I'd sooner sleep under the stars
than in some smoky tent.

599
00:37:01.573 --> 00:37:03.491
What if it rains?

600
00:37:03.492 --> 00:37:05.326
The tree will shelter me.

601
00:37:05.327 --> 00:37:07.579
- Trees leak.
- [scoffs]

602
00:37:09.039 --> 00:37:10.706
So they do.

603
00:37:10.707 --> 00:37:11.959
What's your name?

604
00:37:13.126 --> 00:37:15.628
- Dunk.
- Ser Dunk.

605
00:37:15.629 --> 00:37:18.966
That's no name for a knight.
Is it short for Duncan?

606
00:37:19.800 --> 00:37:22.009
Yeah.
[clearing throat] Yes.

607
00:37:22.010 --> 00:37:23.720
Uh. Ser Duncan of...

608
00:37:28.308 --> 00:37:31.186
[inhales sharply]
Ser Duncan the Tall.

609
00:37:32.145 --> 00:37:33.813
Never heard of him.

610
00:37:33.814 --> 00:37:35.773
Do you know every knight
in the Seven Kingdoms. then?

611
00:37:35.774 --> 00:37:37.233
The good ones.

612
00:37:37.234 --> 00:37:38.485
[scoffs]

613
00:37:40.028 --> 00:37:42.488
- You got a name. thief?
- Egg.

614
00:37:42.489 --> 00:37:43.490
Egg.

615
00:37:45.200 --> 00:37:49.036
Well. Egg. by rights.
I should beat you bloody.

616
00:37:49.037 --> 00:37:50.330
send you on your way.

617
00:37:52.124 --> 00:37:54.000
But you look as though
you don't eat much.

618
00:37:54.001 --> 00:37:55.293
[sighs]

619
00:37:55.294 --> 00:37:57.421
And if you'll swear
to do as you're told...

620
00:37:59.673 --> 00:38:01.174
I'll let you serve me
for the tourney.

621
00:38:04.052 --> 00:38:05.178
After that. well...

622
00:38:07.681 --> 00:38:08.765
we'll see.

623
00:38:11.643 --> 00:38:15.314
I don't have much.
but if you prove worth your keep...

624
00:38:16.940 --> 00:38:19.276
you'll have clothes on your back
and food in your belly.

625
00:38:20.485 --> 00:38:22.903
The clothes might be rough-spun
and the food.

626
00:38:22.904 --> 00:38:24.989
salt beef and salt fish.

627
00:38:24.990 --> 00:38:26.241
but you won't go hungry.

628
00:38:28.160 --> 00:38:29.786
I promise not to beat you.

629
00:38:31.079 --> 00:38:32.706
Except when you deserve it.

630
00:38:33.665 --> 00:38:34.708
Yes. my lord.

631
00:38:36.376 --> 00:38:37.377
"Ser."

632
00:38:39.254 --> 00:38:40.672
I'm only a hedge knight.

633
00:38:46.345 --> 00:38:48.347
- [fire crackling]
- [insects chirring]

634
00:38:50.932 --> 00:38:52.225
[Egg sighs]

635
00:38:53.435 --> 00:38:55.937
A falling star brings luck
to those who see it.

636
00:38:58.357 --> 00:39:00.316
Go to sleep. boy.

637
00:39:00.317 --> 00:39:03.486
All the other knights
are in their pavilions by now.

638
00:39:03.487 --> 00:39:05.906
staring up at silk
instead of sky.

639
00:39:08.075 --> 00:39:09.701
Do you want a clout in the ear?

640
00:39:20.754 --> 00:39:22.839
S-So. the luck is ours alone?

641
00:39:29.596 --> 00:39:32.599
[♪ gentle music playing]

642
00:39:49.366 --> 00:39:52.369
♪
